I finished a BA in Illustration and Visual Media in 2014 at the London College of Communication with a First-class Honours. It was a very broad and flexible course and in a first-year self-initiated project about logic I discovered programming in Processing and was hooked. The degree allowed me to continue to produce work using Processing in various visual and interactive ways, and I later moved on to the web working mostly in Javascript. In 3rd year I wrote my dissertation on the Open Source movement and what this means for designers, wondering if designers adopt the principles of Open Source and also the tools, whether the role of the designer would change from designing an outcome to designing algorithms and generative systems.

Being very interested in all things Open Source I continued to explore what I could learn for free and furthured my knowledge of the web with PHP and MySQL databases, and then on to Python and more recently C++ through OpenFrameworks. I've also dabbled with more esoteric languages such as Donald Knuth's MetaFont. In the past year I have made the commitment to only using Vim as a text editor in an effort to make all aspects of work efficient.

